# Chapter 4: New Equipment
Azeroth is home to a great many intelligent races, each with their own unique set of cultures and craftsmen. From the great dwarven smiths of Ironforge to the brilliant gnomish engineers of Gadgetzan, from the bubbling cauldrons of the undead alchemists of Undercity to the durable leatherwork of the tauren of Mulgore, there are quality creations in every corner of the world.

New forms of nonmagical equipment, from weapons to tools, that originate in this setting are collected in this chapter, to be used alongside the equipment presented in Chapter 5 of the Player's Handbook.

## Magic and Technology
<!-- Goblins and gnomes have shown great ingenuity in using natural materials and science to create items ranging from simple explosives to mechanical lifeforms. Magic is also rather ubiquitous; whether crafted intentionally by spellcasters and craftsmen or arising naturally from the presence or demise of powerful magical creatures, magic items practically litter the world.

Commerce is the lifeblood of any world and Azeroth is no different. Goblins are shameless profiteers, willing to put themselves at risk by conducting trade across faction lines in search of wealth. Additionally, auction houses are common features in large cities, where harvested materials and discovered artifacts are sold to the highest bidder--or whoever is willing to meet the buyout price. 

These elements combined make Warcraft a setting with a very active market goods both magical and mundane. A  -->

Warcraft as a setting is perhaps best described as both *High Magic* and *Sword and Sorcery*, as defined on <br/> page 38 of the Dungeon Master's Guide. Mundane magic equipment is commonplace, particularly in larger cities.

Elven cities such as Silvermoon and Darnassus are renowned for their streetside displays and mystical enclaves, and the floating mage city of Dalaran is said to practically overflow with arcane power. Most other major cities share this phenomena, to some extent; playing host to guilds and orders that dedicate themselves to different magical arts.

Azeroth is also a world of gunpowder, steam engines, and clockwork devices. Some technological creations are so advanced that they blur the line between magic and the mundane. Gnomes and goblins search for oil and esoteric substances to power their sprawling tech-hub cities and settlements.

## Starting Equipment
When you create your character, follow the standard rules located in the Player's Handbook for determining your starting equipment. If you choose the alternative option of starting with a number of gold pieces based on your class, consult the Starting Wealth by Class table below.

##### Starting Wealth by Class
